The paper deals with detecting misclassified and out-of-distribution examples in neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper presents a simple baseline approach that utilizes probabilities from softmax distributions, which is a common technique used in deep learning. The tasks used to assess performance are all related to computer vision, natural language processing, and automatic speech recognition, which are all subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
